{"word":"H1802 - דָּלָה - dâlâh - daw-law' - Draw","slug":"H1802","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דָּלָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dâlâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>daw-law'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Draw"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05DC;&#x05D4; - da&#x0302;la&#x0302;h</b> - <i>daw-law'</i><p/>A primitive root (compare <a href=\"#/H1809\">H1809</a>); properly to <i>dangle</i>, that is, to <i>let down</i> a bucket (for <i>drawing</i> out water); figuratively to <i>deliver: - </i>draw (out), X enough, lift up."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1805\">H1805</a>, <a href=\"#/H1806\">H1806</a>, <a href=\"#/H1808\">H1808</a>, <a href=\"#/H1817\">H1817</a>"}]}